"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082108","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Online Harms White Paper will be published shortly and will set out a range of legislative and non-legislative measures to tackle a range of online harms. DCMS continues to work closely with the games industry and organisations including the Gambling Commission, to improve safety in games and promote healthy and responsible video gaming.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","228666","2019-03-13T14:27:35.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082108/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082108/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-05","Internet: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to publish his White Paper on online harms.","false","Biography information for Laura Smith","Crewe and Nantwich","Laura Smith","228665"
