"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082250","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>Neither DfT ministers or officials have been approached by or met with representatives of the fossil fuel industry to discuss the EcoDrive gadget.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","228620","2019-03-11T14:05:09.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082250/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082250/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Fuels: Consumption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether (a) he, (b) Ministers in his Department and (c) officials in his Department met representatives of the fossil fuel industry to discuss EcoDrive, a gadget to help preserve fuel usage.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","228619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082251","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>Neither DfT ministers or officials have been approached by or met with representatives of the fossil fuel industry to discuss the EcoDrive gadget.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","228619","2019-03-11T14:05:09.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082251/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082251/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Fuels: Consumption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether (a) he, (b) Ministers in his Department and (c) officials in his Department met representatives of the fossil fuel industry to discuss EcoDrive, a gadget to help preserve fuel usage.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","228620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082252","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>The draft statutory guidance on taxi and private hire vehicle licensing which the Department is consulting on is made using powers in the Policing and Crime Act 2017. Section 177 of the Policing and Crime Act 2017 enables the Secretary of State to issue guidance to public authorities as to how their licensing functions under taxi and private hire vehicle legislation may be exercised so as to protect children, and vulnerable individuals who are 18 or over, from harm. The Department does not believe that prohibiting vehicles from undertaking journeys which do not take place or end in the area in which they are licensed falls within scope of the section 177 powers.</p><p>In the response to the report by the Chair of the Task and Finish Group on Taxi and Private Hire Vehicle Licensing Government agreed with the principle that all taxi and private hire vehicle journeys should start and/or end within the area that issued the licences, and set out that further consideration will be given to how this might best work in practice, with a view to legislation.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-03-11T13:23:35.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082252/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082252/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to his Department's consultation entitled Taxi and private hire vehicle licensing: protecting users, published on 12 February 2019, whether he has plans for statutory guidance to prohibit vehicles from undertaking journeys which do not take place or end in the area which they are licensed.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082253","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>The draft statutory guidance proposes a number of measures for licensing authorities to consider when setting taxi and private hire vehicle policy and administration of the regime. Adoption of the recommendations made in the final statutory guidance and any assistance that might be needed for the trade in their area will be a matter for licensing authorities.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-03-11T13:18:54.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082253/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082253/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the consultation on statutory guidance for the licensing of private hire vehicles, whether the Government will provide financial assistance to help vehicle owners make the changes necessary to meet the new regulations.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","228585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082254","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Healthy Start and Nursery Milk schemes are demand led statutory schemes. This means that the Department must meet expenditure arising from legitimate claims made in line with the legislation. Funding is allocated to the schemes to meet the actual demand, rising or falling in line with the overall uptake for each scheme, and the Government works to ensure that eligible people are aware of the schemes and how they can benefit from them.</p><p> </p><p>The funding allocated to the schemes is accounted for through a single cost centre with total costs is shown in the following table. A split by individual scheme is not available in the format requested.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010 - 2011</p></td><td><p>£133,996,866</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011 - 2012</p></td><td><p>£139,569,214</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012 - 2013</p></td><td><p>£141,366,339</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013 - 2014</p></td><td><p>£137,790,212</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014 - 2015</p></td><td><p>£128,904,379</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015 - 2016</p></td><td><p>£124,890,649</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016 - 2017</p></td><td><p>£112,556,870</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017 - 2018</p></td><td><p>£104,709,791</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Audited spend data for the 2018-19 financial year is not yet available.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","228740","2019-03-13T12:25:58.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082254/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082254/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-05","Healthy Start Scheme and School Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 30 April 2018 to Question 140109 on Healthy Start and Nursery Milk schemes, how much funding his Department allocated to the (a) Healthy Start scheme and (b) Nursery Milk Scheme in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2017-18 and (iv) 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","228714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082255","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>The UK Government will work with the devolved administrations to ensure that towns in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland also benefit from the Stronger Towns Fund. We will announce further details in due course.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-03-11T16:44:55.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082255/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082255/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-05","Regeneration: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether the Government plans to allocate to Wales money for community rejuvenation similar to other towns in England.","false","Biography information for Anna McMorrin","Cardiff North","Anna McMorrin","228715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082257","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>Licensing authorities have a duty to ensure that any person to whom they grant a taxi or private hire vehicle driver’s licence to is a fit and proper person to hold such a licence. Licensing authorities remain responsible for ensuring that the drivers they license remain fit and proper throughout the period of the licence.</p><p>The draft statutory guidance to be issued to licensing authorities which Government is currently consulting on recommends measures to ensure authorities are aware of new information that may affect the suitability of individuals to hold a licence, such as clear complaint processes and biannual enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service checks including the barred lists.</p><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-03-11T14:43:05.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082257/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082257/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking with local taxi licensing authorities to ensure that drivers continue to meet standards after the initial granting of their licence.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","228621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082258","Home Office","false","2019-03-12","<p>The Government’s White Paper, “The UK’s future skills-based immigration system” (Cm 9722), published on 19 December 2018, provides a platform for further discussion. We have launched an extensive programme of targeted engagement across the UK, to capture views and ensure that we design a future system that works for every nation.</p><p>There are three approaches to this engagement programme.The Government is engaging with specific sectors to communicate proposals and understand their priorities for a future system. We will hold cross-sector forums in the nine regions of England and all the nations of the UK to hear views from across the country.</p><p>We are also creating advisory groups that will have detailed discussions with private, public and voluntary sector employers and industry representatives as the policy and system is developed</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","228719 ; 228720 ; 228721","2019-03-12T16:33:56.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082258/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082258/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-05","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Immigration White Paper, published in December 2018, if he will publish his Department's engagement proposals as described in that White Paper.","true","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","228716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082259","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-11","<p>The Government’s response to the report by the Chair of the Task and Finish Group on Taxi and Private Hire Vehicle Licensing agreed with the principle that all taxi and private hire vehicle journeys should start and/or end within the area that issued the licences, and set out that further consideration will be given to how this might best work in practice, with a view to legislation.</p><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-03-11T14:40:01.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082259/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082259/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-05","Taxis: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to prevent taxi or private hire vehicle drivers from operating exclusively outside of the locality in which they are licensed.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","228622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082261","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>The UK Government will work with the devolved administrations to ensure that towns in Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland also benefit from the Stronger Towns Fund. We will announce further details in due course.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-03-11T16:46:53.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082261/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082261/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-05","Stronger Towns Fund: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether the Stronger Towns Fund will be replicated in Wales.","false","Biography information for Anna McMorrin","Cardiff North","Anna McMorrin","228717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082262","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-12","<p>The following table sets out interest paid by National Health Service trust and foundation trusts in each year since the introduction of interim revenue support loans:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>2018-19*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>NHS Trust</p></td><td><p>£14,935,544</p></td><td><p>£44,356,477</p></td><td><p>£69,945,307</p></td><td><p>£105,159,539</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Foundation Trust</p></td><td><p>£8,783,806</p></td><td><p>£29,518,357</p></td><td><p>£47,989,946</p></td><td><p>£80,059,239</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>£23,719,350</p></td><td><p>£73,874,834</p></td><td><p>£117,935,253</p></td><td><p>£185,218,778</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br>Note:</p><p>*2018-19 includes interest to be paid in March 2019.</p><p>The interest paid is not lost to the NHS. It is paid to the Department but is channelled back into the NHS through the annual funding provided to the NHS through the NHS England mandate.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2019-03-12T12:37:08.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082262/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082262/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-05","Department of Health and Social Care: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much interest has been paid by NHS trusts and Foundation Trusts on bailout loans from his Department in (a) the last 12 months and (b) each of the last five years; where such interest is paid to; and for what purposes such interest payments were subsequently used.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","228718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082264","Home Office","false","2019-03-12","<p>The Government’s White Paper, “The UK’s future skills-based immigration system” (Cm 9722), published on 19 December 2018, provides a platform for further discussion. We have launched an extensive programme of targeted engagement across the UK, to capture views and ensure that we design a future system that works for every nation.</p><p>There are three approaches to this engagement programme.The Government is engaging with specific sectors to communicate proposals and understand their priorities for a future system. We will hold cross-sector forums in the nine regions of England and all the nations of the UK to hear views from across the country.</p><p>We are also creating advisory groups that will have detailed discussions with private, public and voluntary sector employers and industry representatives as the policy and system is developed</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","228716 ; 228720 ; 228721","2019-03-12T16:33:56.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082264/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082264/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-05","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Immigration White Paper, published in December 2018, what type of engagement he plans to undertake in relation to the proposals described in that White Paper.","true","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","228719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082265","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-11","<p>The Stronger Towns Fund prospectus will be published before Summer recess. This will outline the process for how towns can come forward and will set out the process of the £600 million competitive component of the fund. It will also detail the role of local partners, relevant definitions and eligibility criteria.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-03-11T16:45:18.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082265/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082265/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-05","Stronger Towns Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what the eligibility criteria for the Stronger Towns Fund will be; and whether local authorities can apply to that fund for (a) specific projects or (b) grants for general use.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","228555"
