"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082380","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-13","<p>​We are in regular dialogue with the European Commission and other member states on the human rights situation in Syria, including coordinating with them on human rights resolutions on Syria at the UN Human Rights Council and at the UN General Assembly. We have received no representations from the European Commission or EU member states on human rights abuses against the Syrian people or the Kurdish minority in Syria or elsewhere.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2019-03-13T17:35:13.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082380/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082380/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1082380/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-05","Kurds and Syria: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has received from his counterparts in (a) the European Commission and (b) EU member states on human rights abuses against the (i) Syrian and (ii) Kurdish people.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","228775"
