hat estimate he has made of the number of intra-EU traders who need to register for an EORI number that (a) are and (b) are not already VAT registered.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Bailey","West Bromwich West","Mr Adrian Bailey","227940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081737","Treasury","false","2019-03-12","<p>This £2 million funding to support the cost of training is part of a wider £8 million investment to support the sector ahead of the UK leaving the EU, which includes a further £3 million in grant funding for IT improvements and £3 million which is being used to increase training provision in this area.</p><p> </p><p>Applications are still being received, but as of 5 March 2019 124 applications have been submitted for the training grants available to customs intermediaries and traders who complete customs declarations. Applications are subject to a review process once submitted, and so far 43 training grants have either been offered or have already been paid‎.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-03-12T17:29:34.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081737/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081737/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081737/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-04","Customs Declaration Services Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much of the £2 million allocated to helping traders to make customs declarations has been drawn down by traders upskilling their capacity to make customs declarations; how many grant funding applications have been made to that fund; and many traders have been successful in such applications.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Bailey","West Bromwich West","Mr Adrian Bailey","227941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081738","Treasury","false","2019-03-12","<p>The £5 million grant fund, which includes the £2 million to support customs intermediaries and traders who complete customs declarations with the cost of training, does not include any administration costs. Any costs associated with administering the scheme are accounted for separately. The full £5 million grant fund is available for bids from intermediaries and traders.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-03-12T17:30:33.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081738/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081738/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081738/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-04","Customs Declaration Services Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much of the £2 million allocated to helping traders to make customs declarations has been spent on (a) administering the scheme and (b) helping traders.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Bailey","West Bromwich West","Mr Adrian Bailey","227946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081739","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-03-07","<p>Armed military personnel may only be deployed on UK soil in exceptional circumstances for example, in response to a military invasion or in support of a Civil Authority or Government Department in accordance with Military Aid to the Civil Authorities (MACA).</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-03-07T16:37:34.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081739/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081739/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-03-04","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what (a) reasons and (b) circumstances armed military personnel can be deployed on UK soil.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","228069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081740","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-03-07","<p>Armed military personnel may only be deployed on UK soil in exceptional circumstances, under the Royal Prerogative or in response to regulations made by Order in Council under the Civil Contingencies Act 2004.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-03-07T16:38:43.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081740/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081740/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1081740/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-03-04","Armed Forces: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the UK Parliament has any role on the deployment of armed military personnel on UK soil.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","228070"
